# FQDN allowlist for the devcontainer egress proxy (see squid.conf).
# Loaded by Squid as an `acl ... dstdomain` source file. A leading dot matches
# the bare host plus all subdomains; bare entries match only that host.
#
# This is the project-agnostic baseline: the two coding agents, GitHub, and
# PyPI. Add a project's own endpoints below the marker. After editing, either
# rebuild the container or hot-reload without one:
#   sudo cp .devcontainer/allowed-domains.acl /etc/squid/allowed-domains.acl
#   sudo /usr/sbin/squid -k reconfigure
# A blocked request shows up as TCP_DENIED in `sudo tail -f /var/log/squid/access.log`.

# --- Coding agents ---
# Anthropic / Claude Code (the CLI itself + telemetry + the native installer at
# claude.ai, used by post-create.sh and the background auto-updater).
.anthropic.com
.claude.ai
.claude.com
.sentry.io
# OpenAI / ChatGPT (Codex CLI install script + binary download, auth, API).
.openai.com
.chatgpt.com

# --- Source control / packages ---
# GitHub (git, gh CLI, raw content, container registry).
.github.com
.githubusercontent.com
ghcr.io
# PyPI (pip / uv dependencies).
.pypi.org
.pythonhosted.org

# --- Project-specific endpoints ---------------------------------------------
# Add the hostnames your project needs below, e.g.:
#   .huggingface.co        # model weights
#   .googleapis.com        # Google APIs
# (a leading dot covers all subdomains).
